  "notes": [
    {
      "id": "ddba6f45-6887-ef11-8474-000d3a37e3b6",
      "type": "GeneralTitle",
      "area": "General",
      "position": 0,
      "content": "IMPORTANT MAJOR INFORMATION",
      "contentHtml": null
    },
    {
      "id": "e0ba6f45-6887-ef11-8474-000d3a37e3b6",
      "type": "GeneralText",
      "area": "General",
      "position": 1,
      "content": "This Central and East European Languages and Cultures major concentrates on a language and culture of Central and Eastern Europe such as Czech, Polish, Serbian/Croatian, Ukrainian, Hungarian or Romanian. Students are encouraged to become global citizens by giving them the opportunity to gain insight on one of the largest and most powerful regions in the world. Listed below are the lower division preparation courses for the major. To be considered for admission to this major, you must complete the following courses by the end of spring before transfer: One course in introduction to Central, Eastern Europe and Slavic Civilization is STRONGLY RECOMMENDED and should be completed by the end of spring before transfer. NOTE: If course(s) are not available, applicants must demonstrate sincere interest in the major. All courses must be taken for a letter grade. For more information regarding this major and UCLA's transfer selection process, visit https:// www.slavic.ucla. and https:// admission.ucla.edu . PLEASE NOTE: the community college courses listed below have been approved to satisfy the preparation for this major at UCLA, but they may not be exact equivalents of the UCLA courses listed.",
      "contentHtml": "<p>This Central and East European Languages and Cultures major concentrates on a language and culture of Central and Eastern Europe such as Czech, Polish, Serbian/Croatian, Ukrainian, Hungarian or Romanian. Students are encouraged to become global citizens by giving them the opportunity to gain insight on one of the largest and most powerful regions in the world.</p><p><br></p><p>Listed below are the lower division preparation courses for the major.</p><p><br></p><p>To be considered for admission to this major, you must complete the following courses by the end of spring before transfer:</p><ul><li>One course in introduction to Central, Eastern Europe and Slavic Civilization is <strong>STRONGLY RECOMMENDED</strong> and should be completed by the end of spring before transfer.</li></ul><p>NOTE: If course(s) are not available, applicants must demonstrate sincere interest in the major.</p><p>All courses must be taken for a letter grade.</p><p><br></p><p>For more information regarding this major and UCLA's transfer selection process, visit <u style=\"color: rgb(41, 98, 255);\">https://</u><a href=\"http://www.humnet.ucla.edu/humnet/slavic/undergrad/index.html\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">www.slavic.ucla.</a> and <u style=\"color: rgb(41, 98, 255);\">https://</u><a href=\"http://www.admission.ucla.edu\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">admission.ucla.edu</a>.</p><p><br></p><p>PLEASE NOTE: the community college courses listed below have been approved to satisfy the preparation for this major at UCLA, but they may not be exact equivalents of the UCLA courses listed.</p>"
    },
    {
